\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\lambda=\frac{a\Delta y}{s}=\frac{a'\Delta y(d_{o}-f)^{2}}{d_{o}f^{2}+d_{o}f(d_{o}-f)}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where we have used the thin lens equation to write 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{i}$
\end_inset

 in terms of 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{o}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 in terms of 
\begin_inset Formula $a'$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{o}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

, in order to write the equation in terms of the experimentally measured
 quantities.
 We used a 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{o}$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $61.5\pm0.5$
\end_inset

 cm and a focal length 
\begin_inset Formula $f=40.0\pm0.1$
\end_inset

 cm, and the measured source separation was 
\begin_inset Formula $a'=1.0\pm0.5$
